<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

''kind'' is a lightweight schema engine for TiddlyWiki. Each type's full definition — fields, constraints, title formula, icon, namespace memberships, and stream-river display config — lives on a single tiddler. Instances are plain tiddlers marked with a `kind.type` field. No inheritance, no separate per-field tiddlers, no central registry.

!! Features

* ''Schema-as-tiddler'' — one tiddler per type, with field defs as a JSON array in `kind.fields`
* ''Discovery'' — `[all[shadows+tiddlers]has[kind.type]has[kind.fields]]` finds all type tiddlers
* ''Namespaces'' — types declare `kind.namespaces`, the active scope picks one (or all)
* ''Editor'' — 2-column form (label + input), table-style, with live validation messages
* ''Field Bar'' — auto-rendered in the stream river on every instance; configurable per type; self-disabling
* ''Creator'' — pick a type, fill fields, click Create; title computed from `kind.title-formula`
* ''Validator'' — wiki-wide report of constraint violations
* ''Type-builder'' — structured editor for type metadata + JSON textarea for fields, with live preview
* ''Instances Overview'' (soft-dep on a graph engine) — the ''Kind: Instances Overview'' tiddler renders a whole-wiki graph of every instance. Nodes are coloured per type (palette by sorted type index, or an optional per-type `kind.color` override), seeded onto a stable grid so the layout never reshuffles; dragging a node persists its position to `$:/config/rimir/kind/instances-overview/structure`. A search box filters nodes by caption/title, an ''Edges'' checkbox row toggles which ref-typed fields are drawn as edges (default `parent`), and a colour-coded ''Types'' row shows/hides instances per type (default all shown). Edges are colour- and stroke-coded per ref-field (`kg.edge-color` / `kg.edge-stroke`) and labelled with the field name when more than one field is drawn. The hover tooltip carries per-node actions: ''edit'' opens a modal with the standard live field editor, ''delete'' opens a confirm dialog (disabled with a hint while the node still has `parent`-field children — the modal re-checks the guard at render time), and ''Add child'' buttons appear for every kind whose `parent` ref field accepts the node's type (plus explicit `kind.parent-kinds` children, via `kg.child-kinds`) — the create form pre-fills `parent`, applies field defaults, and reuses `kind.finalize-create`, so title-formula/validation/auto-children behave exactly like the Creator. All three buttons dismiss the tooltip on click and hand over to the `$:/plugins/rimir/kind/graph-modal` overlay (tagged `$:/tags/AboveStory`; layered above the cascade-palette so it also works from the Context side-preview). Needs `flibbles/graph` + a rendering engine; shows an install hint when absent.
* ''Context preview'' (soft-dep on a graph engine + bimlas kin-filter) — a cascade-palette side-preview shown for any kind-instance that draws just that instance's neighbourhood in the `parent` tree, reusing the //Instances Overview// renderer and persisted positions. ''Direction'' pills choose `↓ Descendants` (default) or `↑ Ancestors`, ''Levels'' pills choose how many hops (1–5, default 2), ''Edges'' pills multi-select which ref-fields to draw, and colour-coded ''Types'' pills toggle which kind-types are shown — every setting persists globally under `$:/state/rimir/kind/context/`, and the edge pills carry each relationship's own colour so the row doubles as a legend. The subgraph is selected with `[kin:parent:<dir>:<depth>[<base>]]`. The graph wiring is shared with the overview via the `$:/plugins/rimir/kind/graph` module (the `kg-graph` renderer + `kg.*` functions, incl. `kg.edge-color`/`kg.edge-stroke`), so both views stay in sync.
* ''Notes preview'' (soft-dep on `sq/streams` for the stream parts) — a cascade-palette side-preview (`palette/preview/notes`, `ca-preview-applies: [<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]`) that surfaces everything "noted" about the selected instance. It renders the instance's OWN content first — its `text` body (block-transcluded) and, if it is a Streams root, its note-structure — then every kind-instance that points to it: typed children (`parent` field) unioned with back-ref referrers (every back-navigable ref field, via `kind.qual-source-kinds` / `kind.qual-back-fields` / `kind.referencing-instances`), de-duplicated and sorted `created` descending. Stream child-nodes are excluded from the note list by the `has[kind.type]` gate (they belong to their root's stream block, not the list). A ''View'' pill toggles two layouts, each backed by a `$:/state/rimir/kind/notes/*` tiddler so the toggle refreshes the pane in place (the cp side-preview cache survives a state-only change and dispatches `refresh()` into the live tree): ''Stream'' (default — all notes stacked, newest at top) and ''Tabbed'' (one pill per note, the instance itself leftmost then referrers newest-first, the active note's body shown below; the active pill self-heals to the instance when the stored choice isn't in the current set). Streams render via `$:/plugins/sq/streams/nodes-list-template`, whose double-click in-place editing is pure `$action-*`/`$eventcatcher` (no navigator messages), so it works in the body-mounted palette pane with no `<$navigator>` ancestor; the stream block only renders when streams is installed AND the note has a `stream-list`.
* ''Child kinds'' — set `kind.parent-kinds` to a list of parent type-keys to mark a kind as only creatable from within a parent instance. Hidden from global create surfaces (Creator tab, cascade //Create entity// drill); creatable via the per-instance ''Create here…'' cascade-palette action which also surfaces a ''Create reference'' cluster for any kind that has a ref-typed field pointing back to the host's kind. Type-builder and the cascade //Manage kinds// drill both surface the child kinds of each type (drillable in CP) so the parent-↔-child relationship is visible from either side.
* ''Auto-children'' — set `kind.auto-children` on a parent kind (JSON array of `{kind, fields}` entries) to auto-create child instances every time a parent instance is saved. The child's `parent` field is pre-set to the new parent's title before the child's `kind.title-formula` evaluates, so the child's title can reference the parent. Useful for "every conversation gets a //Conversation Minutes// streams-note" patterns.
* ''Cascade-palette integration'' (soft-dep) — when `rimir/cascade-palette` is installed, kind contributes ''Find by kind'', ''Find entity'', ''Create entity'', and ''Manage kinds'' root entries to the palette. The leader key ''`k`'' jumps straight into the ''Manage kinds'' drill. ''Manage kinds'' is the cascade-mode equivalent of the Type-builder tab: ''+ Create new kind…'' at the root captures a type-key and creates a stub tiddler with the type-builder's defaults; ''+ Clone existing kind…'' picks a source kind, then a text-input row captures the new type-key and clones the schema (`kind.fields` / `kind.title-formula` / `kind.stream-fields` / `kind.namespaces` copied; `kind.type` / `kind.caption` / `kind.icon` blank for the user to set). Drill into an existing kind to edit metadata (caption / icon / namespaces / title-formula / stream-fields), drill into one of its fields to rename the field key (with `kind.stream-fields` auto-sync; instance values stay under the old key) / set typed / caption / icon / cardinality / constraints (toggles for required / unique / unique:wiki; text-edit rows for min:N / max:N; +Add custom constraint…) / options / ref-types via picker sub-stages, ''+ Add field from library…'' picks from common-field defs, ''+ Add new field…'' captures a new field key and creates a row with `typed: text` so it is immediately editable (drill in to change typed / caption / constraints), DEL on a field row removes it with a confirm step, ''DEL on a kind row'' (Manage kinds top-level) removes the kind with a confirm step whose consequence text spells out how many instances would be orphaned (same as the in-drill `🗑 Delete this kind` leaf), ''Ctrl-↑ / Ctrl-↓'' reorder the focused field within `kind.fields` (the array order IS the form field order, so the move propagates to instances created after). Adding a field (either path) auto-appends the key to `kind.stream-fields` (idempotent); deleting a field also removes its key from that list. ''Live create-form preview'' — while drilled into a kind's schema, the palette splits 50/50 and the right pane renders the create-instance form (the same one ''Create entity'' shows) against a per-kind preview-draft tiddler; the form re-renders as the user edits the schema so the effect of every field change is immediately visible. ''Create entity'' opens a draft form with one row per editable field, an optional ''📋 Clone fields from existing <kind>'' drill that picks a source instance and copies its field values into the draft (computed fields and `kind.fields[].clone: skip` excluded), and a ''Save'' leaf whose name previews the computed title (e.g. `💾 Save as "test"`) or swaps to a ''⛔ Cannot save — title-formula yields empty'' row if the formula resolves to empty — the row swaps live as fields fill. ''Ref-field pickers'' also offer ''+ Create new <X>'' (drills into a nested spawn-create flow with its own Save / Clone / field-edit + Cancel via Esc; on Save the new instance is materialised AND linked into the parent's ref field; pops back to the picker with the new ref selected, supports arbitrary nesting depth via the same cascade stack) alongside the existing candidate list. Find by kind / Find entity drill kind → instance lists, with a ''live instance preview'' in the side-preview pane — auto-attached via the cascade-palette tag ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview`'' on `palette/preview/instance-view`. The preview's `ca-preview-applies` filter (`[<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]`) matches any kind-instance row, so ↑/↓ across results updates the read-only card view live. The same preview also auto-attaches during ''+ New <Kind>'' (anchored to the draft tiddler — every field commit on the left re-renders the card on the right) and during the ''Edit fields'' action (anchored to the entity being modified). ''Kind lens'' — kind also ships a ''lens'' (tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/lens`) that appears as the ''Kind'' option in the palette's ''Icon'' slot chooser whenever any kind type is defined. Selected (←→ / ↵ on the ''Kind'' pill in the Icon strip), every menu row backed by a kind instance shows its type's `kind.icon` glyph at the front of the row, across all views; the choice persists across reloads. Off by default. (The lens model — a per-slot single-select decorator that projects a row's name / icon / annotation — supersedes the former cascade-palette ''structure toggle''.)

!! Schema model

* ''Type tiddlers'' — fields `kind.type` (the key), `kind.caption`, `kind.icon`, `kind.namespaces`, `kind.title-formula`, `kind.stream-fields`, and `kind.fields` (JSON array)
* ''Field defs'' — entries inside the JSON array with `key`, `typed`, `caption`, `icon`, `constraints`, `options` (enum), `ref-types` + `cardinality` (ref)
* ''Instance tiddlers'' — any tiddler with `kind.type: <type-key>` is an instance

!! Prerequisites

TiddlyWiki ≥ 5.4.0 in Node.js server mode. No other plugin dependencies. Optional: `$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template` for the documentation hub you're reading right now.

!! Quick start

# Open the ''type-builder'' tab; create a blank type and fill its metadata
# Paste a field-list JSON (see the Examples section)
# Open the ''creator'' tab, pick the type, fill the fields, click Create
# Open the resulting tiddler in the story river — the field bar appears at the top
# Use the ''validator'' tab to scan the whole wiki for constraint violations

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">''Why a new plugin alongside `rimir/typed`?'' typed has accumulated features (3-level inheritance, separate per-field tiddlers, two ref-editor modes, ~1600 lines). kind drops everything that doesn't pay rent in TiddlyWiki's bag-of-fields model and adds namespaces. See the FAQ for details.</$fill>
</$transclude>

